Meritage Portfolio Management Has Lowered Stake in Ingredion INC (INGR) as Share Value Declined


					

						July 24, 2017 - By test

Investors sentiment is 1.09 in Q4 2016. Its the same as in 2016Q3. It has no change, as 41 investors sold INGR shares while 156 reduced holdings. only 52 funds opened positions while 162 raised stakes. 59.87 million shares or 1.89% less from 61.03 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. State Bank Of America De holds 272,963 shares. Cambridge Investment Research Advsrs Incorporated accumulated 0.01% or 3,725 shares. Wellington Shields Mngmt Limited Liability Co has invested 0.09% in Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR). Raymond James Fincl Svcs reported 6,728 shares. British Columbia Invest Management Corporation accumulated 55,508 shares or 0.06% of the stock. Moreover, Federated Investors Pa has 0.15% invested in Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR). 57,326 are owned by Brandywine Global Inv Mgmt Lc. Centurylink Inv Management Com owns 12,757 shares or 0.54% of their US portfolio. Caisse De Depot Et Placement Du Quebec accumulated 0.01% or 22,100 shares. Howe And Rusling owns 147 shares or 0% of their US portfolio. Contravisory Inv reported 81,863 shares or 3.48% of all its holdings. Stifel Fincl owns 52,024 shares for 0.03% of their portfolio. Mcf Advsr Ltd Llc stated it has 0.01% of its portfolio in Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR). Intl Grp reported 141,241 shares. Geneva reported 0.02% of its portfolio in Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR).







Meritage Portfolio Management decreased its stake in Ingredion Inc (INGR) by 56.24% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Meritage Portfolio Management sold 38,740 shares as the company’s stock declined 4.33% while stock markets rallied. The institutional investor held 30,140 shares of the packaged foods company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $3.77 million, down from 68,880 at the end of the previous reported quarter. Meritage Portfolio Management who had been investing in Ingredion Inc for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $8.75 billion market cap company. The stock declined 0.19% or $0.23 reaching $121.76 per share. About 145,913 shares traded. Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR) has declined 2.30% since July 24, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 19.00% the S&P500.
Meritage Portfolio Management, which manages about $1.31B and $915.83M US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Microsoft Corp (NASDAQ:MSFT) by 164,342 shares to 174,062 shares, valued at $10.82 million in 2016Q4, according to the filing. 
 Analysts expect Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR) to report $1.86 EPS on August, 1 before the open.They anticipate $0.13 EPS change or 7.51 % from last quarter’s $1.73 EPS. INGR’s profit would be $133.66M giving it 16.37 P/E if the $1.86 EPS is correct. After having $1.88 EPS previously, Ingredion Inc’s analysts see -1.06 % EPS growth. 
More news for Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR) were recently published by: Seekingalpha.com, which released: “Ingredion: Keep Your Powder Dry” on March 21, 2017. Postandcourier.com‘s article titled: “North Charleston food, beverage ingredient maker expanding operations” and published on July 21, 2017 is yet another important article.
Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR) Ratings Coverage
Among 7 analysts covering Ingredion Inc (NYSE:INGR), 4 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 57% are positive. Ingredion Inc had 15 analyst reports since August 3, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Citigroup maintained it with “Buy” rating and $140 target in Wednesday, June 15 report. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Wednesday, December 16 by Jefferies. The stock has “Buy” rating by Citigroup on Monday, September 14. The stock has “Hold” rating by BMO Capital Markets on Thursday, April 13. On Thursday, September 8 the stock rating was initiated by Societe Generale with “Hold”. The company was upgraded on Friday, January 29 by Stephens. Jefferies maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Wednesday, June 14 report. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Thursday, June 29 by Jefferies. The firm has “Market Perform” rating given on Friday, October 30 by BMO Capital Markets. The stock has “Hold” rating by BMO Capital Markets on Monday, June 26.


